A 23-YEAR-OLD woman from Mpumalanga has been arrested for allegedly stabbing her 30-year-old boyfriend on Sunday, 24 July. According to Brigadier Selvy Mohlala, the shocking incident occurred at Trichardt near Secunda at around 10.30pm. Mohlala said the couple allegedly had an argument which spiralled into a physical fight. “The neighbours reportedly attempted to intervene, however, the man was stabbed to death. “Police as well as the paramedics were informed about the incident and upon arrival, the victim was certified dead,” Mohlala said. ALSO READ: Gunmen rob tavern owner, patrons! He said police have registered a case of murder and arrested the suspect, who is expected to appear at the Secunda Magistrates Court soon. Meanwhile, Mpumalanga police commissioner Lieutenant-General Semakaleng Manamela has urged the public to make use of social services whenever they face challenges in their relationships. “Violence has never resolved any problem, rather it will lead to undesired consequences. We can never condone violence as a solution to any challenge. Domestic violence continues to take the lives of many in our society and we need to join hands to fight this scourge. The suspect has since been arrested and we believe that the law will take its course,” Manamela said.